Now I have a complete picture of the codebase. Let me provide the comprehensive implementation plan.

---

## Server Components Migration Plan for Next.js 16 App Router with Supabase

### Overview of Current Architecture

**Current State:**
- All three pages use `"use client"` directive with `useEffect` for data fetching
- Query functions in `src/lib/supabase/queries/` all use the browser client (`createClient` from `client.ts`)
- Authentication is handled via `useAuth()` hook which subscribes to `onAuthStateChange`
- The server client exists in `server.ts` and is already properly configured with cookies
- Middleware handles session refresh via `updateSession()`

**Key Gotcha - Query Functions Need Server Versions:**
All existing query functions import the browser client:
```typescript
import { createClient } from "@/lib/supabase/client";
```

This will NOT work in Server Components because `createBrowserClient` uses browser-only APIs. You need to create parallel server-compatible versions that accept a Supabase client as a parameter or create new server-specific query files.

---

## Page 1: Home/Explore (`src/app/page.tsx`)

### Current Behavior
- Reads `q` search param from URL
- Local state for `sort` (defaults to "trending")
- `useEffect` fetches guides when sort or query changes
- Renders `SortTabs` (interactive) and `GuideGrid`

### Target Architecture

**Server Component Structure:**
```
src/app/page.tsx (Server Component)
  - Reads searchParams.q and searchParams.sort from props
  - Fetches initial guides server-side
  - Renders ExplorePageClient with initial data

src/app/loading.tsx (NEW)
  - Suspense fallback for the page

src/components/explore/explore-page-client.tsx (NEW Client Component)
  - Manages sort state (if using client-side navigation)
  - OR: Uses URL-based sort with router.push for full SSR
```

**Recommended Approach - URL-Based Sorting (Full SSR):**

The cleanest approach is to put `sort` in the URL as a search parameter. This makes the entire page cacheable and SSR-friendly.

**Server Component (`src/app/page.tsx`):**
```typescript
// NO "use client"
import { createClient } from "@/lib/supabase/server";
import { GuideGrid } from "@/components/gallery/guide-grid";
import { SortTabsServer } from "@/components/gallery/sort-tabs-server";
import type { Guide, SortOption } from "@/types";

interface HomePageProps {
  searchParams: Promise<{ q?: string; sort?: SortOption }>;
}

export default async function Home({ searchParams }: HomePageProps) {
  const { q: query, sort = "trending" } = await searchParams;

  const supabase = await createClient();
  const guides = await fetchGuidesServer(supabase, sort, query);

  return (
    <div>
      <div className="mb-6 flex items-center justify-between">
        <div>
          <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground">
            {query ? `Results for "${query}"` : "Explore"}
          </h1>
          <p className="mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            {query 
              ? `${guides.length} guide${guides.length !== 1 ? "s" : ""} found` 
              : "Step-by-step guides for building with AI"}
          </p>
        </div>
        <SortTabsServer active={sort} query={query} />
      </div>
      <GuideGrid guides={guides} />
    </div>
  );
}
```

**New Server Query Function (`src/lib/supabase/queries/guides.server.ts`):**
```typescript
import type { SupabaseClient } from "@supabase/supabase-js";
import type { Database } from "@/types/database";
import type { Guide } from "@/types";

export async function fetchGuidesServer(
  supabase: SupabaseClient<Database>,
  sort: string = "trending",
  search?: string
): Promise<Guide[]> {
  let query = supabase
    .from("posts")
    .select(`
      *,
      profile:profiles!posts_user_id_fkey(*),
      media:post_media(*)
    `)
    .eq("is_hidden", false);

  if (search) {
    query = query.or(`title.ilike.%${search}%,description.ilike.%${search}%`);
  }

  switch (sort) {
    case "recent":
      query = query.order("created_at", { ascending: false });
      break;
    case "popular":
      query = query.order("likes_count", { ascending: false });
      break;
    case "trending":
    default:
      query = query.order("trending_score", { ascending: false });
      break;
  }

  const { data, error } = await query.limit(24);

  if (error) {
    console.error("Failed to fetch guides:", error.message);
    return [];
  }

  return data as unknown as Guide[];
}
```

